Package: rrfields
Type: Package
Title: Robust Random Fields for Spatiotemporal Modelling
Version: 0.01.9001
Date: 2017-03-27
Authors@R: c(
    person(c("Sean", "C."), "Anderson", email = "sandrsn@uw.edu", 
      role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person(c("Eric", "J."), "Ward", role = "aut"))
Description: Implements Bayesian spatiotemporal models that allow for extreme
    spatial deviations through time. It uses a predictive process approach
    with random fields implemented through a multivariate-t distribution
    instead of a multivariate normal.
License: GPL (>=3)
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.2),
    Rcpp (>= 0.11.0)
Imports:
    rstan (>= 2.14.0),
    ggplot2 (>= 2.2.0),
    cluster,
    dplyr,
    reshape2,
    mvtnorm,
    broom,
    methods,
    assertthat
LinkingTo: StanHeaders (>= 2.14.0), rstan (>= 2.14.0), BH (>= 1.60.0), Rcpp (>=
    0.12.0), RcppEigen
Suggests:
    testthat,
    parallel,
    bayesplot,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    viridis
URL: https://github.com/seananderson/rrfields
